<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="310" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1286,1699]" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1386,1411]" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[360,458,1386,1411]" name="Armenia" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">Armenia</collectingCountry>
eastwards to the Central Asian desert. Since 
<taxonomicName box="[970,1125,1386,1411]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Osmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavicornis">
<emphasis box="[970,1125,1386,1411]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">H. flavicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has often been confounded with other 
<emphasis box="[272,300,1423,1446]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">H.</emphasis>
(
<taxonomicName box="[316,430,1423,1446]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Stenosmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[316,430,1423,1446]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">Stenosmia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) species, its distribution range is poorly known.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1286,1699]" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,351,1458,1483]" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">Pollen hosts.</emphasis>
Possibly oligolectic on 
<taxonomicName box="[633,739,1460,1483]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Tetradiclidaceae" genus="Peganum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="9" pageNumber="310" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[633,739,1460,1483]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">Peganum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[757,902,1458,1483]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Nitrariaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="9" pageNumber="310" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Nitrariaceae</taxonomicName>
): all 
<number box="[961,988,1459,1483]" pageId="9" pageNumber="310" value="11.0">11</number>
pollen loads (
<number box="[1156,1171,1459,1483]" pageId="9" pageNumber="310" value="2.0">2</number>
localities, 
<number box="[1300,1314,1459,1483]" pageId="9" pageNumber="310" value="2.0">2</number>
countries) analyzed so far consisted of 
<taxonomicName box="[477,583,1495,1518]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Tetradiclidaceae" genus="Peganum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="9" pageNumber="310" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[477,583,1495,1518]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">Peganum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
pollen (probably 
<taxonomicName box="[787,911,1494,1519]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Tetradiclidaceae" genus="Peganum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="9" pageNumber="310" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="harmala">
<emphasis box="[787,911,1494,1519]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">P. harmala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), which is in line with 
<bibRefCitation author="Morawitz" box="[1180,1374,1494,1519]" pageId="9" pageNumber="310" refString="Morawitz, F. (1877) Nachtrag zur Bienenfauna Caucasiens. Horae Societatis Entomologicae Rossicae (St. Petersburg), 14, 3 - 112." type="journal article" year="1877">
Morawitz (
<number box="[1306,1366,1495,1519]" pageId="9" pageNumber="310" value="1877.0">1877</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, who observed this species on 
<taxonomicName box="[429,535,1532,1555]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Tetradiclidaceae" genus="Peganum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="9" pageNumber="310" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[429,535,1532,1555]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">Peganum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
flowers in 
<collectingCountry box="[661,763,1530,1555]" name="Armenia" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">Armenia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1286,1699]" box="[199,514,1566,1591]" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,389,1566,1591]" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">Nesting biology.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1286,1699]" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,1602,1627]" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">Notes.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[279,479,1602,1627]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Osmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavicornis">
<emphasis box="[279,479,1602,1627]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">Osmia flavicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the key of 
<bibRefCitation author="Warncke" box="[630,824,1602,1627]" pageId="9" pageNumber="310" refString="Warncke, K. (1991) Die Bienengattung Osmia Panzer, 1806, ihre Systematik in der Westpalaarktis und ihre Verbreitung in der Turkei. 6. Die Untergattung Stenosmia Michener, 1941, comb. nov. (Hymenoptera, Apidae). Entomofauna, 12, 401 - 412." type="journal article" year="1991" yearSuffix="b">
Warncke (
<number box="[744,801,1602,1627]" pageId="9" pageNumber="310" value="1991.0">1991</number>
b)
</bibRefCitation>
is 
<taxonomicName box="[856,1079,1602,1627]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Hoplitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="desertorum" status="spec. nov">
<emphasis box="[856,1079,1602,1627]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">Hoplitis desertorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1086,1192,1603,1626]" pageId="9" pageNumber="310" rank="species">spec. nov</taxonomicNameLabel>
.. The observations on nesting and host plants reported by 
<bibRefCitation author="Marikovskaya" box="[595,844,1638,1663]" pageId="9" pageNumber="310" refString="Marikovskaya, T. P. (1968) New data on the biology of some species of social bees (Hymenoptera, Megachilidae) from southeast Kazakhstan. Entomological Review, 47, 487 - 491." type="journal article" year="1968">
Marikovskaya (
<number box="[777,835,1638,1663]" pageId="9" pageNumber="310" value="1968.0">1968</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
for 
<taxonomicName box="[906,1113,1638,1663]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Osmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavicornis">
<emphasis box="[906,1113,1638,1663]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">Osmia flavicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
probably refer to 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Hoplitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassipunctata" status="spec. nov">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">Hoplitis crassipunctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[323,430,1675,1698]" pageId="9" pageNumber="310" rank="species">spec. nov</taxonomicNameLabel>
.. 
<taxonomicName box="[447,561,1675,1698]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Stenosmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[447,561,1675,1698]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">Stenosmia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. 
<taxonomicName box="[608,759,1674,1699]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Stenosmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aravensis">
aff. 
<emphasis box="[652,759,1676,1699]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">aravensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Praz 
<emphasis box="[852,908,1674,1699]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[923,982,1675,1699]" pageId="9" pageNumber="310" value="2008.0">2008</number>
) is in fact 
<taxonomicName box="[1100,1254,1674,1699]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Osmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavicornis">
<emphasis box="[1100,1254,1674,1699]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">H. flavicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
